Description: Head of terracotta phallus.The tip of a tumescent phallus, probably broken from a figure (Harpocrates). Solid; two-piece mould. Micaceous orange-brown Nile silt with a thick grey core. Probably part of a model group. There are remains of an overall white dressing, painted pink in the grooves defining the glans, but apparently unpainted in the aperture at the very tip.
Bibliographic references: Terracotta / Catalogue of Terracottas in the British Museum (3260)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (DC.126) (Phase 3)
